    </ul>
    <p>This information is collected through standard web server logs and is used to analyze trends, administer the site, and improve our services.</p>

    <h6>1.2 Tool Usage Data</h6>
    <p>When you use our developer tools, most processing happens locally in your browser. However, for certain tools that require server-side processing, we may temporarily process the data you submit. We do not store or log the content you input into our tools.</p>

    <h6>1.3 Authentication Data</h6>
    <p>If you choose to sign in using Google OAuth, we collect basic profile information including your name, email address, and profile photo. This information is used solely for authentication and account management purposes.</p>

    <h5>2. How We Use Information</h5>
    <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul class="browser-default">
      <li>To provide and maintain our services</li>
      <li>To improve and optimize our website and tools</li>
      <li>To monitor usage patterns and analyze trends</li>
      <li>To detect and prevent technical issues and abuse</li>
      <li>To communicate with users when necessary</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h5>
    <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies for:</p>
    <ul class="browser-default">
      <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for the website to function properly, including session management and authentication</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors interact with our website</li>
      <li><strong>Advertising Cookies:</strong> Used by third-party advertising partners (see section 4 below)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings, though disabling certain cookies may affect website functionality.</p>

    <h5>4. Third-Party Services and Advertising</h5>
    
